<TEXT>
the sandinista government on tuesday 
freed 29 peasants accused of collaborating with usbacked rebels 
the first of about 1200 prisoners nicaragua has promised to release 
the 29 were freed from a city jail in this northern town 
this should coincide with the beginning of the demobilization 
of the contras rebels from honduran territory and the withdrawal 
of those who operate in nicaraguan territory president daniel 
ortega said 
he said there will be no mercy for rebel groups who do not 
disband in compliance with the peace agreement signed last week in 
honduras by ortega and four other central american presidents 
ortega spoke at a cermony during the release of the 29 in pantasma 
140 miles north of managua 
he who does not accept the hand we are extending should be 
prepared he said 
under the agreement signed at the summit conference in tela 
honduras the rebels are to disband by early december 
an estimated 11000 contras and 12000 dependents will be moved 
from camps along the honduran border and resettled in nicaragua 
under the accords the government said recently there are about 
2500 contras operating in nicaragua 
in return for the disbanding of the rebels the government has 
pledged to hold free and fair elections in february it would be the 
first free vote since the sandinistas defeated the conservative 
government of president anastasio somoza and gained power in july 
1979 
ortega said the rebels have the opportunity to contribute to 
peace in nicaragua and avoid more suffering for their families 
on sunday ortega agreed to a request from the national union of 
farmers and cattlemen to release about 1200 peasants accused of 
aiding the rebels 
ortega said tuesday that 1515 rebels and 39 former national 
guardsmen in the somoza regime are in nicaraguan prisons 
the government freed 1897 former guardsmen on march 17 
the leftis government has announced monthly ceasefires in its 
war against the rebels since june 1988 when a temporary truce 
between the two sides expired 
pantasma is located in a northern valley the rebels tried to take 
numerous times but failed in october 1983 48 peasants died in the 
fighting 
