<TEXT>
here is a chronology of key events in the case of 
gary dotson cleared monday of rape and aggravated kidnapping 
charges 
 
july 9 1977 cathleen crowell 16 of suburban homewood is 
found by police her body cut and clothes ripped she later 
identifies gary dotson as the man who raped her 
may 24 1979 a circuit court jury in suburban markham finds 
dotson guilty of rape and aggravated kidnapping after miss crowell 
testifies that he was her attacker 
july 12 1979 circuit judge richard samuels sentences dotson to 
25 to 50 years in prison 
march 26 1985 dotsons accuser now cathleen crowell webb 23 
of jaffery nh files an affidavit saying she had sex with a 
17yearold boyfriend in 1977 and concocted the rape story because 
she feared she was pregnant warren lupel dotsons attorney files 
a motion asking samuels to vacate the conviction and free dotson 
may 12 gov james r thompson commutes dotsons sentence to 
time served but refuses to grant a pardon proclaiming dotsons 
innocence dotson is freed 
198687 dotson arrested several times on charges ranging from 
drunken driving to assault imprisoned for violating parole on 
drunken driving conviction 
nov 12 1987 state appeals panel upholds dotsons rape 
conviction despite mrs webbs recantation 
jan 7 1988 circuit judge richard fitzgerald approves an 
agreement that allows genetic tests of evidence in rape case 
aug 17 1988 dotson released from prison after serving six 
months for parole violation enters courtordered alcohol treatment 
program 
july 25 1989 fitzgerald rules that the twoyear statute of 
limitations barring tardy prosecution does not preclude dotson from 
getting a new trial 
aug 14 1989 fitzgerald grants dotson new trial prosecution 
immediately drops all charges against dotson 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

