parties in the coalition discussions should decide on a candidate 
if society wants it i will have to go for the prime ministers 
office walesa said but i would prefer someone else 
walesa also told state tv after we sit down and reach 
agreement on deep reforms then we will find the names to head the 
government too 
he said any solidarityled government would guarantee the 
sensitive ministries of defense and interior to the communist party 
and would do nothing to endanger the functioning of the warsaw 
pact military alliance 
walesa said a solidarity coalition would be a government of 
national responsibility nominated with respect for the rights of 
the polish president referring to the constitutional rights of 
jaruzelski to control foreign policy and the armed forces 
despite such assurances the prospect of a solidarityled 
government has alarmed the communist party and the soviet union 
which has said it could destabilize poland and europe 
the party may also fear a solidarity government would purge the 
nomenklatura party loyalists who hold tens of thousands of 
government and management posts and undermine the communist 
partys main base of support 
the democratic party which along with the peasants holds the 
parliamentary balance of power on tuesday endorsed walesas bid to 
form the next government 
we think that we should do everything to realize lech walesas 
proposal which has broad support said the secretariat of the 
party which historically has been allied to the communists 
walesa said aug 7 that only a government headed by solidarity 
and dominated by noncommunists will have the credibility to solve 
polands political and economic problems 
on the economic front kiszczaks caretaker cabinet said extra 
food supplies are to be directed to larger cities and publicly 
owned shops are to be sold or rented to private food vendors 
walesa praised kiszczaks decision to resign saying it reflected 
a feeling of responsibility and could solve the government 
crisis he said he had nothing personally against gen kiszczak the 
interior minister for eight years 
the resignation of a communist premier because the opposition 
wont endorse him as well as the bid by solidarity to form a 
government against the wishes of the polish and soviet party 
authorities demonstrates how radically east bloc politics have 
changed the events would have been unthinkable a year ago 
cardinal jozef glemp the countrys roman catholic primate noted 
the changes during an annual assumption day sermon in czestochowa 
these events and changes of great significance were made 
finally without violence and destruction and we should thank 
god for that he said but he warned the crowd of 150000 of new 
concerns including the economy 
solidarity began coalition talks thursday with lamakers from the 
two minor parties which have a combined strength of 103 seats and 
hold the balance of power in parliament normally obscure and once 
regarded as little more than communist fronts the parties have been 
thrown into the role of kingmakers 
aleksander bentkowski the leader of the peasant partys 
parliament delegation said he favors solidaritys concept for the 
next government 
about a third of the peasant party legislators are leaning to 
solidarity and want greater independence from the communists 
malinowski represents the more traditional procommunist wing of 
the party that claims 500000 members 
since partially free elections in june many of the minorparty 
lawmakers feel that in order to survive they must distance 
themselves from the generally unpopular communists 
