activists to get their opinions on what must be done 
among them were the parents of a texas college student killed by 
members of a drug cult 
jim and helen kilroy among about three dozen people meeting with 
bush and bennett later said tougher enforcement is needed their 
sons body was found in a mass grave outside matamoros mexico 
drug treatment experts said after the meeting that they didnt 
dwell on where to get the money for the antidrug fight 
geraldine sylvester head of new hampshires drug rehabilitation 
services said i dont know how the funds are going to be 
reallocated but i know there is a total commitment to fight this 
war on drugs on all levels and if there has to be some shuffling of 
resources im certain they are astute enough to figure out exactly 
how to do that 
