<TEXT>
armand hammer elated over his pardon by 
president bush for a watergateera crime won a 13year battle to 
clear his name with the same persistence and political savvy that 
made him a multibillionaire industrialist and intimate of world 
leaders 
hammer 91 said on monday he had been pardoned for making 
illegal contributions to president nixons reelection campaign in 
1972 hammer had pleaded guilty to the charges in 1976 and was 
sentenced to one years probation and fined 3000 
white house officials confirmed that bush had pardoned hammer and 
nine other unidentified people on monday but refused to give 
details repeated efforts to reach presidential counsel c boyden 
gray were unsuccessful tuesday 
having spent my lifetime fighting injustice this vindication 
reinforces my abiding faith in the american system of justice 
hammer said in a statement from his los angeles home i deeply 
appreciate president bushs action in clearing my name 
a spokesmen said tuesday that hammer chairman of occidental 
petroleum corp would have no further comment 
hammer spent several years seeking a pardon president reagan is 
known to have considered granting hammers wish before he left 
office last january but nothing came of it 
im pleading guilty because im guilty hammer had declared 
in federal court in 1976 but hammer had blamed former gov tim 
babcock of montana a former vice president of an occidental 
subsidiary through whom the 54000 in illegal payments were made 
hammer argued that he funneled the money through babcock to 
maintain anonymity but that babcock did not deliver the funds until 
after a new federal law went into effect in april 1972 which 
prohibited making campaign contributions in someone elses name 
babcock was sentenced to four months in prison and fined 1000 
for concealing the identity of hammer as the actual donor a federal 
judge later set aside babcocks prison term partly because hammer 
was given probation instead of a prison term because of his age and 
poor health 
leaving his hospital bed as a heart patient for sentencing 13 
years ago hammer expressed regret over the first crime he had ever 
committed he told the judge that i trust in the time that may be 
left me your honor will allow me to continue being a useful member 
of society 
since his brush with the law hammer has circled the globe in his 
specially outfitted boeing 727 hobnobbing with presidents kings and 
prime ministers pushing for ussoviet summit talks providing aid 
to earthquake victims giving away chunks of his vast art collection 
and trying to raise 1 billion to find a cure for cancer 
ive had two dreams two ambitions in life and i hope to 
accomplish both of them he once said they are peace between east 
and west and a cure for cancer 
all the while hammer has guided occidental petroleums growth 
from a struggling oil company worth 34000 in 1956 when he made 
his first investment into a colossus of oil chemicals coal and 
foods with a book value of more than 6 billion 
his pardon was not universally applauded however 
a group called the friends of oliver north decried the pardon for 
the man they said has been trying to encourage communist expansion 
through his open business dealings with the soviet union the 
group called on bush to muster the courage to pardon north the 
former white house aide convicted of charges in the irancontra 
affair 
born in new york as the grandson of a russian jewish immigrant 
hammer became a millionaire while still studying at columbia 
university when he took over his physician fathers faltering 
pharmaceutical business and turned it into a moneymaker 
at 23 he was fresh out of medical school but unwilling to wait 
six months to begin his internship at new yorks bellevue hospital 
so in 1921 hammer made his first trip to the soviet union to help 
alleviate a typhus epidemic 
once there hammer decided the russian people needed food more 
than medical assistance he quickly announced a deal that brought a 
shipload of surplus american wheat valued at 1 million in return 
for russian furs hides and caviar 
that deal caught the attention of vi lenin the first of many 
soviet leaders hammer has known lenin encouraged the young american 
entrepreneur to take over an abandoned asbestos mine near western 
siberia the first soviet concession ever granted to a foreigner 
hammer developed the mine into a profitable enterprise and soon 
obtained sales concessions for such leading american firms as ford 
motor co us rubber allischalmers and underwood typewriter he 
also opened the soviet unions first pencil factory which posted 1 
million in profits in the first year 
hammer left the soviet union in 1930 taking his profits in the 
form of paintings tapestries silver and jewels which formed the 
start of his multimilliondollar art collection he owns two art 
galleries in new york city 
during the 1940s hammer netted a 75 million profit from a 
100000 investment by developing a way to turn surplus potato crops 
into commercial alcohol and marketing a blended whiskey under his 
own label he accumulated seven distilleries and later sold his 
entire whiskey interests to the schenley group 
he also made fortunes in livestock feed and cattle and held the 
nations first milliondollar purebred angus cattle sale even 
today he is reaping fat profits from a 20 billion chemical 
fertilizer deal with the soviets and has joint coal mining and 
phosphoric acid ventures under way in china 
commenting on his reputation as a worldwide wheelerdealer 
hammer once said i am first a catalyst i bring people and 
situations together thats the big thing bringing the deal 
together 
</TEXT>
