a boeing corp subsidiary overcharged the 
government by 59 million on five computer projects between 1983 
and 1987 a house committee said tuesday 
rep john conyers dmich chairman of the house government 
operations committee released a report from the general accounting 
office the congressional auditing agency detailing the overcharges 
by boeing computer services co like gao conyers said he was asking 
the air force to seek recovery of the money 
